  "prompt": "Does money laundering fall under criminal legislation?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering falls under criminal legislation in most countries. It is typically considered a serious financial crime that involves concealing the origins of illegally obtained money. Specific legal approaches and penalties can vary by jurisdiction, but money laundering is generally criminalized and prosecuted under:\n\n1. Criminal codes\n2. Anti-money laundering (AML) statutes\n3. Financial crime legislation\n\nPenalties often include:\n- Substantial fines\n- Imprisonment\n- Asset seizure\n- Criminal record\n\nMany countries have specific laws and regulatory frameworks designed to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities.",
